<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4610914>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 53. Articulated right forelimb of the holotype of Temnocyon ferox (YPM-PU 10787), John Day Formation, Oregon. The forefoot shows elongation of the paraxonic metacarpals 3, 4, and their digits, with reduction of metacarpals 1, 2, and 5 (metacarpal 5 is hidden from view). A partial femur (fe) and tibia (ti) of an oreodont were entombed with the beardog. Abbreviations: sc, scapula; hu, humerus, ul, ulna; ra, radius; cp, carpus; nos. 1–4, metacarpals; pr, proximal phalanx; ip, intermediate phalanx." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4610914/files/figure.png" .

